Charges laid over fire set outside gate to PM’s residence
OTTAWA—Charges have been laid against a man who allegedly set a small fire outside Prime Minister Stephen Harper’s official residence.
Daniel Skahan, a 29-year-old from Ottawa, has been charged with mischief under $5,000, possession of incendiary material and failure to comply with conditions of an assessment order.
Police say Skahan has mental health issues and is known to them. He has been referred to the mental health court.
Skahan allegedly poured a small quantity of flammable liquid on the sidewalk outside the gates to 24 Sussex Dr. and set it alight Saturday night.
The Mounties responsible for security at the residence immediately apprehended him and turned him over to Ottawa police. There were no injuries or significant property damage.